<TITLE> Back injury rules Dhoni out of first Test </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 16 (bdnews24.com)  India suffered a major blow on the eve of the first Test against Bangladesh starting here on Sunday with news that MS Dhoni will not lead the side due to a back strain. Virender Sehwag will be acting skipper while Dinesh Karthik will assume wicketkeeping responsibilities, Indian team manager Arshad Ayub confirmed on Saturday. Dhoni suffered a back spasm during morning practice, retired to the dressing room and sent Sehwag for the traditional captain's pre-match conference. Speaking to journalists Ayub said: "The spasm continued and refused to go away. Dhoni didn't want to take any chances and decided at the team meeting in the evening that he wouldn't play the Test. Karthik will replace him
